Write f2 block jackknife estimates to disk

write_f2.Rd

This function takes a 3d array of f2 block jackknife estimates, splits it by population pair, and writes each pair to a separate .RData file.

write_f2(f2_block, path, overwrite = FALSE)

Arguments

f2_block

3d array with f2 block jackknife estimates. The first two dimensions of f2_block have to have population names. Each file will be stored under {path}/{pop1}/{pop2}.RData.
path

directory into which to write the files.
overwrite

should existing .RData files be overwritten?

See also

read_f2

Examples

if (FALSE) {
write_f2(f2_block, path = 'path/to/f2stats/')
}
